The well-acknowledged OER process is based on the adsorbate evolution mechanism (AEM), by which the oxygen-containing adsorbates undergo catalytic reactions on the surface-active TM cations of the catalyst. Therefore, the AEM could be regarded as the redox reactions of metal cations. On the whole, the oxygen generation in alkaline media follows Eq. 1, which is accompanied with the transfer of four electrons.14OH-→O2+2H2O+4e-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
